The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Attack on widows home
                                                                                                               Attack on widows home
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Krishnagar, March 20: A mob of nearly 1,000 ransacked the house of a 70-year-old widow in Krishnagar after her maid was found dead at her doorstep this afternoon.        
	The body of 40-year-old Smriti Biswas  with injury marks on the neck  was discovered by her husband Mantu, a cycle van operator.        
	Mantu led the mob to Kalyani Biswass house, alleging that she had a hand in the murder.         
	Police, however, are waiting for the post-mortem report before lodging a murder case.        
	Kalyani lives with her daughter Supriya, also a widow, and granddaughter. The younger women were away in Santiniketan when the house was raided.         
	About 1,000 people  Mantus neighbours in nearby Sukulpara  armed with sticks, sickles and stones, marched to Kalyanis house around 2pm. They dragged the widow out and began breaking everything in sight. The TV, refrigerator, washing machine, DVD player and furniture were smashed to pieces.         
	The mob also hurled stones and set fire to portions of the three-storey building.        
	Mantu said he had gone to Kalyanis house meet his wife and found her dead at Kalyanis doorstep. He alleged that Kalyani used to physically abuse Smriti.                                                                                                                                                                              
